  "prompt": "What problems would you like Uber to solve for you with their app?",
  "response": "There are several potential improvements and features that could enhance the Uber experience:\n\n1. **Improved ETA Accuracy**: More precise estimated time of arrival (ETA) based on real-time traffic conditions and historical data to help users plan better.\n\n2. **Enhanced Safety Features**: Adding more safety options, such as an emergency contact notification system, live ride tracking for friends and family, and improved driver background checks.\n\n3. **Multi-Stop Rides**: More intuitive options for setting multiple stops on a single ride, allowing users to easily drop off multiple passengers or run errands.\n\n4. **Ride Scheduling Flexibility**: The ability to more easily adjust or cancel scheduled rides and receive reminders or alerts closer to the pickup time.\n\n5. **Better Payment Options**: Introducing more local payment methods, the ability to split fares easily with friends, and a loyalty rewards program.\n\n6. **In-App Communication**: Improved messaging features to communicate with drivers without needing to reveal phone numbers, including predefined text options for common questions.\n\n7. **Feedback Mechanism**: A more transparent feedback system where users can see how their ratings and comments impact the service and drivers.\n\n8. **Sustainability Options**: Easy access to eco-friendly ride options, such as electric vehicles or carpooling, along with information on carbon emissions savings.\n\n9. **Accessibility Features**: Enhanced support for riders with disabilities, including better options and information regarding vehicle accessibility.\n\n10. **Real-Time Support**: More efficient customer support options, including live chat within the app for faster resolution of issues during a ride.\n\n11. **Integrated Public Transportation**: A feature to integrate Uber with public transit information, allowing users to plan the best journey using a combination of Uber and other transport options.\n\n12. **Enhanced Driver Profiles**: More comprehensive driver profiles that include ratings, driver history, and vehicle details to give riders more insight before a ride.\n\nAddressing these areas could significantly enhance user satisfaction and overall experience with the Uber app.",
